original_title: Manhattan: New Chambers Street - Roosevelt Street
text:
New Chambers Street, south side, east from Roosevelt Street. Also shown is Roosevelt Street, at, adjoining and south of its intersection with New Chambers Streets. The little building at the apex is No. 6 New Chambers Street; all the other buildings go through and face on both streets.

September 9, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

No's. 6,8,10,12,14, and 12 Broome Street, at, adjoining and west of the N. W. corner of Tompkins Street. Also shown is Tompkins Street, west side, north from Broome to Delancey Streets. Note the East River (Williamsburg) Bridge arching Tompkins Street. These buildings are numbered as above. The corner block is 6 to 14 inclusive.

P. L. Sperr.
